WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.093 --> 00:00:12.345
Silvermane.
In charge of organize crime for 30 years.

2
00:00:12.346 --> 00:00:15.181
<i>Someone burned down his mansion
a couple of nights ago.</i>

3
00:00:15.182 --> 00:00:17.267
-  Addison!
- You keep following me.

4
00:00:17.268 --> 00:00:18.685
it won't end the way you want it to.

5
00:00:18.686 --> 00:00:20.770
<i>This guy have superpowers?
Like you?</i>

6
00:00:22.690 --> 00:00:24.607
Do me favor. Hold off on printing that.

7
00:00:24.608 --> 00:00:26.901
<i>I want to warn Donegal
before he gets himself killed.</i>

8
00:00:26.902 --> 00:00:28.361
That's enough of that.

9
00:00:28.362 --> 00:00:29.863
There's gonna be a free-for-all.

10
00:00:29.864 --> 00:00:31.865
The people could use a hero.

11
00:00:31.866 --> 00:00:33.491
I hope they find someone.

12
00:00:33.492 --> 00:00:36.327
I can't help but wonder
what Ruby would think.

13
00:00:36.328 --> 00:00:37.829
<i>I'm not that guy anymore.</i>

14
00:00:37.830 --> 00:00:39.372
<i>Any chance</i>

15
00:00:39.373 --> 00:00:40.373
you know who this is?

16
00:00:40.374 --> 00:00:41.416
Oh. that's Cat Hardy.

17
00:00:41.417 --> 00:00:43.084
<i>Star attraction over at The Alcove.</i>

18
00:00:43.085 --> 00:00:44.586
<i>Is there somewhere we can talk?</i>

19
00:00:44.587 --> 00:00:45.712
- It's business.
- Flint.

20
00:00:45.713 --> 00:00:46.755
<i>Despite what I do.</i>

21
00:00:46.756 --> 00:00:48.006
I don't enjoy hurting people.

22
00:00:52.720 --> 00:00:55.180
- Don't hurt him.
- What the hell is this?

23
00:00:55.181 --> 00:00:57.640
- Just leave us alone. please.
-  <i>When someone</i>

24
00:00:57.641 --> 00:00:58.725
tells you what they are.

25
00:00:58.726 --> 00:01:00.643
- you have to listen.
-  And what is he?

26
00:01:00.644 --> 00:01:02.604
Retired.

27
00:01:02.605 --> 00:01:04.147
I came here to offer him a job.

28
00:01:04.148 --> 00:01:06.859
My friend you met last night--
he's disappeared.

29
00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:14.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

30
00:01:34.178 --> 00:01:35.303
You were saying Flint's your bodyguard.

31
00:01:35.304 --> 00:01:38.556
Yes. He protects me and he is loyal.

32
00:01:38.557 --> 00:01:40.099
Hard to find these days.

33
00:01:40.100 --> 00:01:42.936
No kidding. I didn't marry my husband
for his looks.

34
00:01:42.937 --> 00:01:45.939
What else can you tell us?
Does he have family. friends?

35
00:01:45.940 --> 00:01:48.191
I don't know anything
about his personal life.

36
00:01:48.192 --> 00:01:49.693
I know his address.

37
00:01:50.778 --> 00:01:53.989
Are we gonna talk about the fact that
he turned into some kind of sand monster?

38
00:01:55.783 --> 00:01:57.076
What I know. she knows.

39
00:01:58.410 --> 00:02:00.245
It started about six months ago.

40
00:02:00.246 --> 00:02:02.247
Slow. at first.

41
00:02:02.248 --> 00:02:04.332
But it's been getting worse.

42
00:02:04.333 --> 00:02:06.668
And he never remembers when it happens?

43
00:02:06.669 --> 00:02:08.336
Oh. he always remembers.

44
00:02:08.337 --> 00:02:11.214
Unless he gets clubbed in the head
with an iron girder.

45
00:02:12.341 --> 00:02:15.802
That's it? He turned into sand. That's--
It was sand. right?

46
00:02:15.803 --> 00:02:17.387
Just seems like kind of. like. a big deal.

47
00:02:17.388 --> 00:02:20.390
So. do you have any clues
as to what's causing this to happen?

48
00:02:20.391 --> 00:02:21.933
You haven't given us much to go on.

49
00:02:21.934 --> 00:02:23.810
Isn't that what the money's for?

50
00:02:23.811 --> 00:02:25.436
You're an investigator.

51
00:02:25.437 --> 00:02:27.231
Investigate.

52
00:02:28.232 --> 00:02:30.191
You know. an artist
doesn't just paint with air.

53
00:02:30.192 --> 00:02:32.735
He needs a canvas. brushes. paint.

54
00:02:32.736 --> 00:02:35.154
Do you think I'm withholding
from you. Mr. Reilly?

55
00:02:35.155 --> 00:02:36.447
What if I said I did?

56
00:02:36.448 --> 00:02:37.782
I'd ask why you thought that.

57
00:02:37.783 --> 00:02:39.826
- I'd say a lifetime of experience.
- With clients?

58
00:02:39.827 --> 00:02:41.828
With… women.

59
00:02:43.289 --> 00:02:45.164
As fun as this little game is. I'm afraid

60
00:02:45.165 --> 00:02:47.584
I have other business to attend to.

61
00:02:47.585 --> 00:02:49.587
Get to painting. Mr. Reilly.

62
00:02:58.721 --> 00:03:00.054
What do you think?

63
00:03:00.055 --> 00:03:02.390
I think you might need a cold shower.

64
00:03:02.391 --> 00:03:03.893
I think I might need one.

65
00:03:06.270 --> 00:03:08.146
But you're right.

66
00:03:08.147 --> 00:03:09.898
She is hiding something.

67
00:03:09.899 --> 00:03:11.150
All the fun ones do.

68
00:03:11.817 --> 00:03:13.568
I'm gonna check out Flint's apartment.

69
00:03:13.569 --> 00:03:14.819
Why don't you do down to the Bu--

70
00:03:14.820 --> 00:03:17.530
Bureau of Criminal Records? Yeah.

71
00:03:17.531 --> 00:03:19.449
Been a while since we've had a real case.

72
00:03:19.450 --> 00:03:20.784
But it ain't been that long.

73
00:03:23.537 --> 00:03:26.164
<i>♪ You got to accentuate ♪</i>

74
00:03:26.165 --> 00:03:28.249
<i>♪ the positive ♪</i>

75
00:03:28.250 --> 00:03:30.919
<i>♪ eliminate the negative ♪</i>

76
00:03:30.920 --> 00:03:34.839
<i>♪ and latch on to the affirmative ♪</i>

77
00:03:34.840 --> 00:03:38.009
<i>♪ Don't mess with Mr. In-Between ♪</i>

78
00:03:38.010 --> 00:03:40.428
<i>♪ You got to spread joy ♪</i>

79
00:03:40.429 --> 00:03:42.347
<i>♪ up to the maximum ♪</i>

80
00:03:42.348 --> 00:03:45.808
<i>♪ bring gloom down to the minimum ♪</i>

81
00:03:45.809 --> 00:03:47.894
- <i>♪ and have faith ♪
- ♪ Amen ♪</i>

82
00:03:47.895 --> 00:03:49.729
<i>♪ or pandemonium's ♪</i>

83
00:03:49.730 --> 00:03:51.941
<i>♪ liable to walk upon the scene ♪</i>

84
00:03:53.442 --> 00:03:54.859
<i>♪ Amen ♪</i>

85
00:04:01.450 --> 00:04:04.286
Gonna meet a new supplier
at the docks tomorrow.

86
00:04:05.454 --> 00:04:06.913
Canadian.

87
00:04:06.914 --> 00:04:08.331
You didn't tell me that.

88
00:04:08.332 --> 00:04:09.750
I'm telling you now.

89
00:04:11.043 --> 00:04:14.754
It's not smart for you to go out in public
till we know who tried to take you out.

90
00:04:14.755 --> 00:04:16.506
I'll go where I want.

91
00:04:16.507 --> 00:04:19.175
With all due respect.
you don't pay me what you pay me

92
00:04:19.176 --> 00:04:21.135
for my charm or disposition.

93
00:04:21.136 --> 00:04:25.098
You pay me to keep you alive
and I'm telling you it's a bad idea.

94
00:04:25.099 --> 00:04:28.726
If you dying benefitted me.
I would have done it myself ten years ago.

95
00:04:28.727 --> 00:04:31.187
But I know what I'm good at.
I know what I'm not.

96
00:04:31.188 --> 00:04:34.107
and I need you to stay alive and in power.

97
00:04:34.108 --> 00:04:36.776
So. pretty please. with cherries on top.

98
00:04:36.777 --> 00:04:38.319
let me go down to the docks ahead of you.

99
00:04:38.320 --> 00:04:40.530
Once I make sure everything's kosher.
you can waltz on in

100
00:04:40.531 --> 00:04:42.533
and show everyone
the brightness of your feathers.

101
00:04:43.534 --> 00:04:45.035
You finished?

102
00:04:48.706 --> 00:04:50.456
Problem is not that the guy is out there.

103
00:04:50.457 --> 00:04:53.710
The problem is they thought
they could take me out at all.

104
00:04:53.711 --> 00:04:56.170
Ever since The Spider disappeared.

105
00:04:56.171 --> 00:04:58.131
things have been comfortable.

106
00:04:58.132 --> 00:05:01.259
Maybe someone's thinking
that I got complacent.

107
00:05:01.260 --> 00:05:02.761
Or soft.

108
00:05:03.679 --> 00:05:04.763
Maybe you're one of them.

109
00:05:06.557 --> 00:05:08.474
Thinking you could take me out.

110
00:05:08.475 --> 00:05:10.810
If you could set yourself on fire

111
00:05:10.811 --> 00:05:13.229
like Addison. then you might have a shot.

112
00:05:13.230 --> 00:05:16.482
Imagine controlling that kind of power.

113
00:05:16.483 --> 00:05:19.027
Now Flint goes missing.

114
00:05:19.028 --> 00:05:20.611
Right after.

115
00:05:20.612 --> 00:05:23.364
He's been acting strange lately.

116
00:05:23.365 --> 00:05:25.659
And if those two things are related...

117
00:05:26.577 --> 00:05:27.661
Go look for Flint.

118
00:05:32.416 --> 00:05:34.667
And when the boys find that PI...

119
00:05:34.668 --> 00:05:36.002
Reilly.

120
00:05:36.003 --> 00:05:37.504
Bring him straight to me.

121
00:05:53.270 --> 00:05:55.938
{\an8}<i>♪ The colors fading from the photograph ♪</i>

122
00:05:55.939 --> 00:05:57.690
<i>♪ I could tell the story ♪</i>

123
00:05:57.691 --> 00:06:00.359
<i>♪ but still you wouldn't know the half ♪</i>

124
00:06:00.360 --> 00:06:03.154
{\an8}<i>♪ This love was brought to life
from shards of glass ♪</i>

125
00:06:03.155 --> 00:06:05.239
{\an8}<i>♪ When you kiss me there's a shifting ♪</i>

126
00:06:05.240 --> 00:06:07.700
<i>♪ in the sepia tone ♪</i>

127
00:06:07.701 --> 00:06:10.912
{\an8}<i>♪ Can't escape the madness.
baby. magnetism ♪</i>

128
00:06:10.913 --> 00:06:14.248
{\an8}<i>♪ Run away but something
pulls me back into it ♪</i>

129
00:06:14.249 --> 00:06:17.376
{\an8}<i>♪ Lately I've been staring
at a broken mirror ♪</i>

130
00:06:17.377 --> 00:06:20.838
<i>♪ Needing someone to call my own ♪</i>

131
00:06:20.839 --> 00:06:24.050
<i>♪ Hey. lover ♪</i>

132
00:06:24.051 --> 00:06:26.928
{\an8}<i>♪ I need someone to save me now ♪</i>

133
00:06:26.929 --> 00:06:29.180
{\an8}<i>♪ from all the pain ♪</i>

134
00:06:29.181 --> 00:06:31.641
{\an8}<i>♪ I suffer ♪</i>

135
00:06:31.642 --> 00:06:34.477
{\an8}<i>♪ and the heavy world
that weighs me down ♪</i>

136
00:06:34.478 --> 00:06:38.022
{\an8}<i>♪ 'Cause the world ain't sweet ♪</i>

137
00:06:38.023 --> 00:06:40.399
{\an8}<i>♪ It's bitter to taste ♪</i>

138
00:06:40.400 --> 00:06:41.776
{\an8}<i>♪ But you could be ♪</i>

139
00:06:41.777 --> 00:06:44.988
<i>♪ my saving grace ♪</i>

140
00:07:34.705 --> 00:07:35.956
Great.

141
00:07:47.426 --> 00:07:48.509
<i>Hi. this is</i>

142
00:07:48.510 --> 00:07:50.511
- Robbie Robertson calling.
-  <i>Mr. Robertson.</i>

143
00:07:50.512 --> 00:07:53.848
<i>how many times do I have to tell you?
You're never getting your old job back.</i>

144
00:07:53.849 --> 00:07:56.893
Listen. I don't know if Walters
has seen my article in the Gazette.

145
00:07:56.894 --> 00:07:59.270
- but I just-- I--
<i>- Mr. Robertson. there's no point...</i>

146
00:07:59.271 --> 00:08:01.772
What I'm saying is I j--
I-I just need to sit with him. that's all.

147
00:08:01.773 --> 00:08:04.400
<i>- Mr. Roberston. please. Mr. Robertson.</i>
- But if you-if you just...

148
00:08:04.401 --> 00:08:06.652
<i>- I'm going to hang up now.</i>
- ...you would just give me a chance to--

149
00:08:06.653 --> 00:08:08.779
I'm onto something truly sensational!

150
00:08:08.780 --> 00:08:10.323
It's the biggest story in years.

151
00:08:10.324 --> 00:08:12.576
There hasn't been anything this big
since The Spider.

152
00:08:15.162 --> 00:08:17.998
I promise it'll be worth his while.

153
00:08:21.627 --> 00:08:23.462
<i>I'll see what I can do.</i>

154
00:08:25.422 --> 00:08:27.924
Thank you. Thank you.

155
00:08:29.092 --> 00:08:32.178
<i>Flint Marko?</i>

156
00:08:32.179 --> 00:08:34.305
<i>Got a delivery.</i>

157
00:08:34.306 --> 00:08:35.932
Anybody home?

158
00:08:35.933 --> 00:08:37.183
Come on...

159
00:09:21.812 --> 00:09:23.689
Flint.

160
00:09:27.526 --> 00:09:29.236
<i>Addison!</i>

161
00:09:32.864 --> 00:09:34.740
Flint.

162
00:09:34.741 --> 00:09:37.369
It's Winston.
Silvermane wants to talk to you.

163
00:09:38.370 --> 00:09:40.538
Gimme the keys.

164
00:09:52.551 --> 00:09:54.261
Check the bedroom.

165
00:10:46.855 --> 00:10:48.565
Nice place.

166
00:10:50.484 --> 00:10:53.194
Yeah. Bit fancy for my taste.

167
00:10:53.195 --> 00:10:56.364
And I got a pretty good idea why.

168
00:10:56.365 --> 00:10:57.449
Why?

169
00:10:58.325 --> 00:10:59.700
Let's go.

170
00:10:59.701 --> 00:11:01.243
You think he got a new lady?

171
00:11:01.244 --> 00:11:04.080
That why he ain't coming to poker lately?

172
00:11:11.046 --> 00:11:14.090
<i>♪ If you're blue and you don't know
where to go to ♪</i>

173
00:11:14.091 --> 00:11:17.927
<i>♪ why don't you go where fashion sits? ♪</i>

174
00:11:17.928 --> 00:11:19.887
<i>♪ Puttin' on the Ritz...</i>

175
00:11:19.888 --> 00:11:22.723
Janet. Long time.

176
00:11:22.724 --> 00:11:24.100
Thought you might've wised up
and quit the biz.

177
00:11:24.101 --> 00:11:25.976
Oh. no. not me. Hank.

178
00:11:25.977 --> 00:11:28.063
Sad to report I'm dumb as ever.

179
00:11:29.523 --> 00:11:31.524
Found this sitting outside.

180
00:11:31.525 --> 00:11:33.359
I didn't know if it belonged to anyone.

181
00:11:33.360 --> 00:11:34.944
Hmm.

182
00:11:34.945 --> 00:11:36.821
<i>♪ with their swell beaus...</i>

183
00:11:36.822 --> 00:11:38.948
Ooh.

184
00:11:38.949 --> 00:11:40.950
You know my wife
made me quit eating these.

185
00:11:40.951 --> 00:11:42.159
Okay. well. in that case...

186
00:11:42.160 --> 00:11:45.204
Hey! Last I checked. you ain't my wife.

187
00:11:45.205 --> 00:11:46.956
<i>♪ Puttin' on the Ritz...</i>

188
00:11:46.957 --> 00:11:49.208
- Name?
- Flint Marko.

189
00:11:49.209 --> 00:11:51.001
All right. Be right back.

190
00:11:51.002 --> 00:11:52.461
Don't you dare touch that bag.

191
00:11:52.462 --> 00:11:54.797
It ain't a bribe if I don't get to eat it.

192
00:11:54.798 --> 00:11:56.590
<i>♪ Puttin' on ♪</i>

193
00:11:56.591 --> 00:11:57.758
-  Janet. good to see you.
- <i>♪ the Ritz...! ♪</i>

194
00:11:57.759 --> 00:11:59.761
Oh! Hey. Charlie. How you been?

195
00:12:03.056 --> 00:12:06.016
Quite the record. our Mr. Marko.

196
00:12:06.017 --> 00:12:09.353
Grew up in Brooklyn. Working class.
Came back with no prospects.

197
00:12:09.354 --> 00:12:11.605
Small crimes. then bigger ones.

198
00:12:11.606 --> 00:12:14.191
Arrest. arrest. arrest.

199
00:12:14.192 --> 00:12:16.152
Now an enforcer for--

200
00:12:16.153 --> 00:12:17.778
Silvermane.

201
00:12:17.779 --> 00:12:20.157
That Winston guy showed up
while I was at Flint's.

202
00:12:20.866 --> 00:12:23.326
- You hid in the closet?
- I hid in the closet.

203
00:12:25.078 --> 00:12:26.454
Meuse-Argonne.

204
00:12:26.455 --> 00:12:28.289
Didn't you fight there too?

205
00:12:28.290 --> 00:12:30.833
Yeah.
Was one of the biggest battles of the war.

206
00:12:30.834 --> 00:12:32.168
There were a million of us there.

207
00:12:32.169 --> 00:12:35.212
- Hold on. Is that--
- Addison.

208
00:12:35.213 --> 00:12:36.755
Looks like they were in the war together.

209
00:12:36.756 --> 00:12:39.300
Is that what Cat is hiding from you?

210
00:12:39.301 --> 00:12:42.094
I bet she knew that Flint
had a friend with superpowers.

211
00:12:42.095 --> 00:12:44.930
Oh. I know. What I don't know
is why she didn't tell me.

212
00:12:44.931 --> 00:12:46.765
Probably thought
you wouldn't have taken the case.

213
00:12:46.766 --> 00:12:48.642
She would've been right.

214
00:13:24.304 --> 00:13:26.180
I don't think I've ever heard that one.

215
00:13:26.181 --> 00:13:28.015
I wouldn't think so.

216
00:13:28.016 --> 00:13:29.518
It's an original.

217
00:13:31.895 --> 00:13:34.189
Visited Flint's apartment today.

218
00:13:36.733 --> 00:13:38.275
This mean anything to you?

219
00:13:38.276 --> 00:13:40.569
I knew he was in the war.

220
00:13:40.570 --> 00:13:43.113
Hard to believe he was ever so young.

221
00:13:43.114 --> 00:13:44.907
What about this guy?

222
00:13:44.908 --> 00:13:46.492
You see him--
this little guy. right over here?

223
00:13:46.493 --> 00:13:49.496
He ever come around The Alcove.
visit Marko?

224
00:13:50.956 --> 00:13:52.457
Can't say I've ever seen him.

225
00:13:53.833 --> 00:13:56.961
His name's... Addison.

226
00:13:56.962 --> 00:13:59.755
He's the guy that
burned down Silvermane's mansion.

227
00:13:59.756 --> 00:14:01.590
He's dead now.

228
00:14:01.591 --> 00:14:03.343
So's the PI that shot him.

229
00:14:03.927 --> 00:14:07.638
What can I say?
The world's a dangerous place.

230
00:14:12.102 --> 00:14:13.894
You're pretty cool under pressure.

231
00:14:13.895 --> 00:14:15.729
- I wasn't aware I was under any.
- Why didn't you tell me

232
00:14:15.730 --> 00:14:18.482
- Flint worked for Silvermane?
- Would you have taken the case if I had?

233
00:14:18.483 --> 00:14:19.483
- I don't like surprises.
- I'll remember that

234
00:14:19.484 --> 00:14:21.152
when your birthday rolls around.

235
00:14:24.406 --> 00:14:26.448
The deed is under my name.

236
00:14:26.449 --> 00:14:29.535
but it's no secret
Silvermane owns this place.

237
00:14:29.536 --> 00:14:32.454
And Flint's a good way
to protect his investment.

238
00:14:32.455 --> 00:14:34.457
- And you.
- And me.

239
00:14:35.750 --> 00:14:38.877
You see. this club lives and dies
on people walking through that door

240
00:14:38.878 --> 00:14:40.839
because they want what I give them.

241
00:14:44.175 --> 00:14:46.093
You trying to get me. Mr. Reilly?

242
00:14:46.094 --> 00:14:48.012
"Get you"?

243
00:14:48.013 --> 00:14:49.680
Understand me.

244
00:14:49.681 --> 00:14:51.181
Seems you got my number.

245
00:14:51.182 --> 00:14:53.309
I've learned a lot of them over the years.

246
00:14:53.310 --> 00:14:55.686
Oh. o-one for every Tom. Dick and Harry?

247
00:14:55.687 --> 00:14:58.147
Hmm. You're interesting.

248
00:14:58.148 --> 00:15:00.274
Oh. yeah? How's that?

249
00:15:00.275 --> 00:15:03.694
Well. the other night when we met.
you called yourself a coward.

250
00:15:03.695 --> 00:15:06.071
But I think you're braver than you let on.

251
00:15:06.072 --> 00:15:08.490
Oh you're good.

252
00:15:08.491 --> 00:15:10.743
In an obvious sort of way.

253
00:15:10.744 --> 00:15:12.620
I'm as subtle as the situation requires.

254
00:15:12.621 --> 00:15:15.039
You see. I have business with Silvermane

255
00:15:15.040 --> 00:15:17.124
and I have business with you. Mr. Reilly.

256
00:15:17.125 --> 00:15:18.959
One has nothing to do with the other.

257
00:15:18.960 --> 00:15:22.172
Now. have I said enough for you
to keep the money you came here to return?

258
00:15:23.256 --> 00:15:24.840
Or have I misjudged you?

259
00:15:24.841 --> 00:15:27.509
No I'll keep working the case.

260
00:15:27.510 --> 00:15:29.095
Not because I'm brave.

261
00:15:30.180 --> 00:15:31.555
- Why. then?
- Uh.

262
00:15:31.556 --> 00:15:33.807
a singer's got to know all the numbers.

263
00:15:33.808 --> 00:15:37.186
Maybe a detective has just
got to know all the answers.

264
00:16:33.993 --> 00:16:35.036
Uh...

265
00:16:37.080 --> 00:16:38.872
It's. uh...

266
00:16:38.873 --> 00:16:40.582
It.. Tai chi.

267
00:16:40.583 --> 00:16:42.292
Yeah. that's right. It's tai chi.

268
00:16:42.293 --> 00:16:43.794
It's. uh. it's good.

269
00:16:43.795 --> 00:16:47.339
It's good for breathing and relaxation.

270
00:16:47.340 --> 00:16:48.757
I recommend it.

271
00:16:50.051 --> 00:16:52.386
We don't have the slightest clue
what you're talking about.

272
00:16:52.387 --> 00:16:53.972
We don't care. either.

273
00:16:56.307 --> 00:16:58.143
Oh!

274
00:17:01.938 --> 00:17:03.856
A toaster? Really?

275
00:17:03.857 --> 00:17:05.941
Gosh. I shouldn't have thrown it so hard.

276
00:17:15.660 --> 00:17:18.537
-  Come on. Come on.
-  Let's go for a ride.

277
00:17:27.630 --> 00:17:29.548
Mind telling me why I'm here?

278
00:17:29.549 --> 00:17:31.008
Silvermane wants to see you.

279
00:17:31.009 --> 00:17:33.635
I figured that. I'm asking why.

280
00:17:33.636 --> 00:17:35.512
We're not really the "why" guys.

281
00:17:35.513 --> 00:17:38.474
Maybe you wouldn't be here
if you didn't try ripping the boss off.

282
00:17:38.475 --> 00:17:39.850
Ah. Donegal.

283
00:17:39.851 --> 00:17:41.268
I didn't have anything

284
00:17:41.269 --> 00:17:42.478
to do with his little scheme.

285
00:17:42.479 --> 00:17:44.146
I actually tried to talk him out of it.

286
00:17:44.147 --> 00:17:46.774
Like I said. the boss just wants to talk.

287
00:17:46.775 --> 00:17:50.444
And I've got no idea who hired Addison
to burn down your boss' house.

288
00:17:50.445 --> 00:17:52.112
You don't know nothing. huh?

289
00:17:52.113 --> 00:17:53.947
Double negative.
but we'll set that aside for now.

290
00:17:53.948 --> 00:17:55.657
My point is I'm not much of a detective.

291
00:17:55.658 --> 00:17:57.284
Yeah. then you got nothing to worry about.

292
00:17:57.285 --> 00:17:58.619
Just like Donegal. right?

293
00:17:58.620 --> 00:18:01.413
Yeah. just like Donegal.

294
00:18:01.414 --> 00:18:04.208
Uh. by the way. I am sorry about the nose.

295
00:18:04.209 --> 00:18:07.002
Me? That was him.

296
00:18:07.003 --> 00:18:08.796
Oh! Oh...

297
00:18:12.675 --> 00:18:14.511
Get out!

298
00:18:20.683 --> 00:18:22.267
Where'd he go?

299
00:18:22.268 --> 00:18:23.895
Check the side.

300
00:18:30.860 --> 00:18:32.444
The boss ain't gonna like this.

301
00:18:32.445 --> 00:18:34.447
Yeah. he wanted us to bring him in.

302
00:18:35.782 --> 00:18:37.616
Get in the car.

303
00:18:37.617 --> 00:18:39.118
Dumbass.

304
00:18:47.043 --> 00:18:49.086
<i>Times are tough all over.</i>

305
00:18:49.087 --> 00:18:51.964
But the true measure of a city

306
00:18:51.965 --> 00:18:54.758
is in how it responds to the hard times.

307
00:18:54.759 --> 00:18:58.178
And this isn't Topeka or Kalamazoo.

308
00:18:58.179 --> 00:18:59.680
This is New York.

309
00:18:59.681 --> 00:19:02.516
We're gonna link arms and stand strong

310
00:19:02.517 --> 00:19:05.185
against the rising tide.

311
00:19:05.186 --> 00:19:07.688
It was easy to stand up here
when the streets...

312
00:19:07.689 --> 00:19:10.065
What's the headline here?

313
00:19:10.066 --> 00:19:13.277
"Desperate Morris Delivers Dud."

314
00:19:13.278 --> 00:19:15.404
No. I'd-I'd go with quadruple M:

315
00:19:15.405 --> 00:19:17.573
"'Mayor's Missive Misses Mark."

316
00:19:17.574 --> 00:19:19.157
Man. I wouldn't trust Hudson

317
00:19:19.158 --> 00:19:22.327
to do my laundry and that man's
gonna beat Morris by ten points.

318
00:19:22.328 --> 00:19:25.831
Sometimes you just
want a different brand of snake oil.

319
00:19:25.832 --> 00:19:29.334
So. uh. you gonna explain your face?

320
00:19:29.335 --> 00:19:32.171
Let's just say you should
lay off the Addison reporting.

321
00:19:33.423 --> 00:19:35.007
Silvermane?

322
00:19:35.008 --> 00:19:38.093
He's on a warpath about Addison.
Wants to know who's coming after him.

323
00:19:38.094 --> 00:19:40.637
So tread... lightly.

324
00:19:40.638 --> 00:19:44.141
Man. I'm not the one with a face
that looks like hamburger meat.

325
00:19:44.142 --> 00:19:46.351
I've tangoed with his guys before.

326
00:19:46.352 --> 00:19:48.854
As the man with the mask and the goggles.

327
00:19:48.855 --> 00:19:51.648
New York's beloved hero of the hour.

328
00:19:51.649 --> 00:19:53.317
Not as Ben Reilly.

329
00:19:53.318 --> 00:19:54.818
You know what? Gimme that.

330
00:19:54.819 --> 00:19:56.904
I'm making a declaration right now.

331
00:19:56.905 --> 00:19:58.697
That's right.

332
00:19:58.698 --> 00:20:00.866
If I'm re-elected

333
00:20:00.867 --> 00:20:02.951
you can say goodbye to Prohibition.

334
00:20:02.952 --> 00:20:04.703
Man knows his audience.

335
00:20:04.704 --> 00:20:08.540
As God is my witness.
you'll never go thirsty again.

336
00:20:10.043 --> 00:20:13.170
Look. all I'm saying
is you're in it with Silvermane now.

337
00:20:13.171 --> 00:20:15.547
If the choice is to suit up or die.

338
00:20:15.548 --> 00:20:17.299
might be time to tango again.

339
00:20:17.300 --> 00:20:19.801
Maybe you'd be doing the city a favor
in the process.

340
00:20:19.802 --> 00:20:22.262
Oh. come on. Robbie. Enough of that.

341
00:20:22.263 --> 00:20:23.680
You know what I'm doing after this?

342
00:20:23.681 --> 00:20:25.557
- What?
- Being beautiful.

343
00:20:25.558 --> 00:20:28.727
And working the Addison story.

344
00:20:28.728 --> 00:20:31.314
I don't publish. I don't eat. my friend.

345
00:20:33.650 --> 00:20:35.652
I've been thinking about the Canadians.

346
00:20:36.903 --> 00:20:38.403
You gonna let me handle it?

347
00:20:38.404 --> 00:20:40.948
No. I'll do it.

348
00:20:40.949 --> 00:20:43.325
Plan stands. but...

349
00:20:43.326 --> 00:20:45.995
go ahead of me. Scout it out.

350
00:20:50.583 --> 00:20:52.459
Ah.

351
00:20:52.460 --> 00:20:54.503
I think it's stylish.

352
00:20:54.504 --> 00:20:56.089
What do you think. Winston?

353
00:20:57.173 --> 00:20:58.757
I'm not one for fashion.

354
00:20:58.758 --> 00:21:01.426
But the whole thing is a little...

355
00:21:01.427 --> 00:21:03.011
tired.

356
00:21:03.012 --> 00:21:06.182
Now. Winston.
have you got a gripe with her?

357
00:21:07.475 --> 00:21:11.311
No. I just think there's better things
to spend time on than dressing up dolls.

358
00:21:12.397 --> 00:21:14.856
Well. there's fashion and there's taste.

359
00:21:14.857 --> 00:21:18.610
Box it up. You like it too. right?

360
00:21:18.611 --> 00:21:19.820
Honestly. I think it's--

361
00:21:19.821 --> 00:21:21.531
Yeah. yeah. it's perfect.

362
00:21:40.091 --> 00:21:42.719
Excuse me. ma'am.
I'm looking for the Addisons.

363
00:21:55.690 --> 00:21:57.191
Mrs. Addison?

364
00:22:28.181 --> 00:22:29.682
Who are you?

365
00:22:34.520 --> 00:22:37.230
- Hey. brother.
- Don't "hey. brother" me.

366
00:22:37.231 --> 00:22:38.857
I asked you a question.

367
00:22:38.858 --> 00:22:40.150
You sure did.

368
00:22:40.151 --> 00:22:43.028
and seeing as you are a very large

369
00:22:43.029 --> 00:22:44.571
- and angry man.
- Mm.

370
00:22:44.572 --> 00:22:45.822
I'm gonna answer.

371
00:22:45.823 --> 00:22:47.657
I'm looking for Vera Addison.

372
00:22:47.658 --> 00:22:49.618
Know where she is?

373
00:22:49.619 --> 00:22:50.994
Why do you want to know?

374
00:22:50.995 --> 00:22:52.871
Well. I am a reporter.

375
00:22:52.872 --> 00:22:54.998
Working a story on James Addison's death.

376
00:22:54.999 --> 00:22:57.418
Wanted to talk to his widow.

377
00:23:00.171 --> 00:23:01.672
Jimmy's dead?

378
00:23:04.217 --> 00:23:06.677
Oh. I'm sorry.
You... you guys were friends?

379
00:23:07.845 --> 00:23:09.347
How did he die?

380
00:23:10.431 --> 00:23:11.933
Mm. there was an explosion...

381
00:23:13.976 --> 00:23:16.269
...at the Standard Oil depot.

382
00:23:16.270 --> 00:23:18.021
Why are you writing about him?

383
00:23:18.022 --> 00:23:21.191
Well. before he died
he burned down the wrong house.

384
00:23:21.192 --> 00:23:22.776
Whose?

385
00:23:22.777 --> 00:23:24.278
Silvermane.

386
00:23:32.620 --> 00:23:33.829
- Think it's time for you to leave.
- Wait. wait.

387
00:23:33.830 --> 00:23:35.455
wait. wait. wait. wait. wait.
wait. wait. wait. wait.

388
00:23:35.456 --> 00:23:37.332
Addison didn't just take it

389
00:23:37.333 --> 00:23:40.293
upon himself to burn down the house
of the most dangerous man in the city.

390
00:23:40.294 --> 00:23:42.045
Someone paid him to do it.

391
00:23:42.046 --> 00:23:45.590
Now. look. he was your friend.
so I'm guessing he wasn't a bad guy.

392
00:23:45.591 --> 00:23:47.134
He was sick.

393
00:23:47.135 --> 00:23:50.679
And these days call for men
to use their sicknesses to get by.

394
00:23:50.680 --> 00:23:53.140
Until their sicknesses eat them alive.

395
00:23:53.141 --> 00:23:55.601
- Hang on. what do you mean. he was sick?
- I don't know who hired him.

396
00:23:57.061 --> 00:23:58.812
But. yeah.

397
00:23:58.813 --> 00:24:00.355
his wife might.

398
00:24:00.356 --> 00:24:02.065
And do you know where I can find her?

399
00:24:02.066 --> 00:24:03.817
Try the Geoffrey Hotel.

400
00:24:03.818 --> 00:24:05.944
She always went there
when they came into some money.

401
00:24:05.945 --> 00:24:07.654
And when she came back.

402
00:24:07.655 --> 00:24:09.281
the money was gone.

403
00:24:09.282 --> 00:24:10.991
Go figure.

404
00:24:10.992 --> 00:24:13.326
Well. thanks.

405
00:24:13.327 --> 00:24:14.829
I'll pay her a visit.

406
00:24:17.832 --> 00:24:19.958
I told you.

407
00:24:19.959 --> 00:24:21.918
he hardly comes to the office anymore.

408
00:24:21.919 --> 00:24:23.879
I can't remember the last time I saw him.

409
00:24:23.880 --> 00:24:27.215
Well. maybe this'll jog your memory.

410
00:24:27.216 --> 00:24:29.217
Please! I'm telling you the truth.

411
00:24:31.304 --> 00:24:33.597
For your sake. I hope so.

412
00:24:33.598 --> 00:24:35.348
We'll be back.

413
00:24:50.489 --> 00:24:51.489
Janet!

414
00:24:51.490 --> 00:24:53.159
Did they hurt you?

415
00:24:54.368 --> 00:24:57.621
No. not this time.
But they said they'd be back.

416
00:24:58.915 --> 00:25:01.374
Ben. they put a gun to my head.

417
00:25:01.375 --> 00:25:03.335
They kept saying that
I'd end up like Donegal?

418
00:25:03.336 --> 00:25:05.879
That if I didn't tell them where you were.

419
00:25:05.880 --> 00:25:08.882
he and I'd be crossing
the River Styx together.

420
00:25:08.883 --> 00:25:10.718
What does that mean?

421
00:25:11.969 --> 00:25:13.887
It means Donegal's dead.

422
00:25:13.888 --> 00:25:15.972
Silvermane killed him.

423
00:25:15.973 --> 00:25:17.933
But I'll take care of it.

424
00:25:17.934 --> 00:25:21.728
Ever since Ruby died. I've been waiting
for you to get it back together.

425
00:25:21.729 --> 00:25:25.023
Back to the man I know
is buried somewhere inside you.

426
00:25:25.024 --> 00:25:26.692
Five years.

427
00:25:28.236 --> 00:25:29.946
And this is how it ends.

428
00:25:31.030 --> 00:25:32.572
Janet.

429
00:25:32.573 --> 00:25:34.282
Go home. Get-get some rest.

430
00:25:34.283 --> 00:25:36.911
You'll feel better and I'll…
I'll call you when it's safe.

431
00:25:37.995 --> 00:25:39.497
Yeah. I'm gonna go home.

432
00:25:41.207 --> 00:25:42.791
But I am not coming back.

433
00:25:42.792 --> 00:25:45.543
I care about you. Ben.

434
00:25:45.544 --> 00:25:47.046
so deeply.

435
00:25:48.297 --> 00:25:50.299
But not enough to die for you.

436
00:25:51.509 --> 00:25:52.718
Janet...

437
00:25:53.803 --> 00:25:56.305
Janet!

438
00:26:44.478 --> 00:26:46.313
Hiya! I'm Pete with Maintenance.

439
00:26:46.314 --> 00:26:48.148
Sorry about the leak.
It'll be no problem.

440
00:26:48.149 --> 00:26:50.400
I'll just. uh-- Gosh. the unit downstairs.

441
00:26:50.401 --> 00:26:52.402
big mess. Water. water everywhere.

442
00:26:52.403 --> 00:26:54.112
- What's going on?
- Something about a leak?

443
00:26:54.113 --> 00:26:56.990
Oh. I like what you've done with place.
Although if you move the table

444
00:26:56.991 --> 00:27:00.535
over by the window.
you really get that sunset glow at dinner.

445
00:27:00.536 --> 00:27:02.996
- I told you that.
- I'm sorry. have you been here before?

446
00:27:02.997 --> 00:27:06.834
I am familiar with the unit. yes.
Uh. bathroom's that way. hmm?

447
00:27:25.978 --> 00:27:28.396
Well. don't just stand there.
Say something.

448
00:27:28.397 --> 00:27:31.484
Um. sir. w-what exactly are you fixing?

449
00:27:32.318 --> 00:27:34.319
Uh. yep. yeah. I found the issue.

450
00:27:34.320 --> 00:27:36.988
You've got a busted gerry casket.

451
00:27:36.989 --> 00:27:38.948
It's a misalignment

452
00:27:38.949 --> 00:27:41.285
from the mission joist.

453
00:28:03.516 --> 00:28:05.726
Excuse me.
w-what's happening in there?

454
00:28:06.894 --> 00:28:09.397
Bit of an existential crisis.
if I'm honest.

455
00:28:11.190 --> 00:28:13.025
About my toilet?

456
00:28:29.959 --> 00:28:31.794
I don't think that guy was a plumber.

457
00:28:54.024 --> 00:28:55.651
Stairs are to the left.

458
00:28:57.319 --> 00:28:58.821
Thanks for your trouble.

459
00:29:00.823 --> 00:29:02.616
Thanks for the dollar.

460
00:29:04.910 --> 00:29:06.745
Mrs. Addison?

461
00:29:09.290 --> 00:29:10.874
I didn't order anything.

462
00:29:10.875 --> 00:29:13.543
My name is Robbie Robertson.
I'm a reporter.

463
00:29:13.544 --> 00:29:17.088
Hold-hold-- ho-hold on.
hold on now. I just...

464
00:29:17.089 --> 00:29:18.673
- I just want to talk.
- You got three seconds

465
00:29:18.674 --> 00:29:20.758
to get out of here or I'm gonna scream.

466
00:29:20.759 --> 00:29:22.594
And I don't think you want
a white woman screaming

467
00:29:22.595 --> 00:29:25.097
about a Black man trying
to force his way into her hotel room.

468
00:29:26.682 --> 00:29:28.975
Actually. I got a hunch...

469
00:29:28.976 --> 00:29:31.352
that you wouldn't want
the city's most ruthless gangster

470
00:29:31.353 --> 00:29:35.190
knowing that the money someone
paid your husband to kill him

471
00:29:35.191 --> 00:29:37.275
was being spent on...

472
00:29:37.276 --> 00:29:40.320
lobster and designer clothes.

473
00:29:40.321 --> 00:29:43.364
So. go ahead and scream. honey.
Unless you want me to do it.

474
00:29:43.365 --> 00:29:45.950
I got a pretty deep voice.
It really carries.

475
00:30:08.516 --> 00:30:10.099
<i>So. that's it?</i>

476
00:30:10.100 --> 00:30:11.935
What do you mean?

477
00:30:11.936 --> 00:30:15.104
No tears?
I just told you your husband died.

478
00:30:15.105 --> 00:30:17.316
People grieve in different ways.

479
00:30:19.109 --> 00:30:21.278
You already knew.

480
00:30:22.780 --> 00:30:26.366
James was a lot of things.
but not the type to cut and run.

481
00:30:26.367 --> 00:30:29.786
When he didn't come home that night.
I figured he was never coming home.

482
00:30:29.787 --> 00:30:32.580
- When did he start setting fires?
- Six months ago.

483
00:30:32.581 --> 00:30:35.291
Suddenly discovered
he had an innate talent for it.

484
00:30:35.292 --> 00:30:36.919
Who hired him for the Silvermane job?

485
00:30:38.170 --> 00:30:41.381
Just because I didn't scream
doesn't mean I'm an open book.

486
00:30:41.382 --> 00:30:43.508
As far as I'm concerned.

487
00:30:43.509 --> 00:30:46.177
James dug his own grave
and now he's lying in it.

488
00:31:02.820 --> 00:31:04.737
This place feels haunted.

489
00:31:04.738 --> 00:31:06.532
That's 'cause it is.

490
00:31:08.576 --> 00:31:10.911
Speaking of ghosts...

491
00:31:12.496 --> 00:31:14.038
...Jimmy Addison's dead.

492
00:31:14.039 --> 00:31:15.541
What?

493
00:31:16.709 --> 00:31:17.959
When?

494
00:31:17.960 --> 00:31:20.169
Couple days ago.
Some reporter came around

495
00:31:20.170 --> 00:31:23.423
asking about him. Wanted to know
who hired him to kill Silvermane.

496
00:31:27.094 --> 00:31:28.177
You didn't know.

497
00:31:28.178 --> 00:31:30.598
If I'd known. I would have stopped him.

498
00:31:39.106 --> 00:31:40.648
Flint.

499
00:31:40.649 --> 00:31:42.109
You don't look so good.

500
00:31:43.193 --> 00:31:45.403
It happened again.

501
00:31:45.404 --> 00:31:47.363
I changed completely this time.

502
00:31:47.364 --> 00:31:49.032
Never changed back.

503
00:31:49.033 --> 00:31:50.784
Eh. not all the way.

504
00:31:52.202 --> 00:31:54.121
It's like the doc said.

505
00:31:55.289 --> 00:31:56.957
Our clocks are ticking.

506
00:31:58.751 --> 00:32:00.627
Faster and faster now.

507
00:32:00.628 --> 00:32:02.504
Everything we went through.

508
00:32:05.215 --> 00:32:07.675
We deserve better. you and I.

509
00:32:07.676 --> 00:32:09.260
Let's get out of here.

510
00:32:09.261 --> 00:32:11.346
You can crash at my place.

511
00:32:11.347 --> 00:32:14.015
Better for us to stick together right now.

512
00:32:15.976 --> 00:32:17.645
Yeah.

513
00:32:18.520 --> 00:32:21.856
You have to check every crate?
Is it 'cause we're Canadians?

514
00:32:21.857 --> 00:32:24.275
Yeah. it's 'cause
you're Canadian. No.

515
00:32:24.276 --> 00:32:27.153
Boss doesn't trust anyone.
Myself included.

516
00:32:27.154 --> 00:32:29.989
That's why he still runs this town.

517
00:32:29.990 --> 00:32:31.824
Shipment's good. boss.

518
00:32:31.825 --> 00:32:33.242
Ready for you to come.

519
00:32:33.243 --> 00:32:35.703
<i>Right. I'm on my way.</i>

520
